Government of Benelux State Bank of Fortis
The Benelux states will help the Belgian-Dutch bank Fortis, which was the first in Europe to get into trouble due to the spreading effect of the crisis of the US mortgage market, by partial nationalization: three countries will support the monetary and insurance institution, which has a capital share of 11 billion euros, also in Hungary.
The Belgian, Luxembourg and Dutch governments agreed to this at the highest level this weekend, with the participation of the President of the European Central Bank and the European Commissioner for Competition.
Banka Fortis is the first in the euro area to be hit by a major crisis in the context of the international financial markets crisis, which has been spreading in waves for more than a year, and the decisions taken in this regard could be seen as precedents in some respects.
According to the decision, which was born on Sunday night, all three states will buy almost half (49 percent) of the bank's assets there.
The bank will sell with absolute certainty a part of its capital holdings, especially - mainly insurance - activities purchased last year from the Dutch bank ABN Amro.
Shares of Fortis Bank began to fall sharply last week, in the second half of the week there were already serious signs of crisis in the institution.
Analysts agree, however, that with its 85,000 employees, the bank is too big to let it crash.
The company's securities fell 12 percent on Friday, to a 14-year low.
Since January, the value of shares has fallen by more than two-thirds.
Given the current share prices, the total market capital value of the group is around EUR 14 billion, but this is unrealistic, according to the company’s executives.
The company’s management is also blaming the collapse of Fortis’ overseas-market uncertainty related to the adoption of a $700 billion U.S. package plan.
Stocks have already risen slightly on Monday.
On Friday, the new CEO, Filip Dierckx, was appointed as the head of the bank.
The money institute was also looking for private buyers, but with a more serious offer, no one has signed up yet.
The Belgian government has already announced that investors do not have to worry, they will not lose their money.
There has been no panic among the bank's clients and the branches have not been attacked.
In Hungary, Fortis Bank has a separate branch and has also acquired several leasing companies.
The fox in the henhouse
Life and health insurance companies in the United States often reject the possibility of concluding an insurance contract with a candidate based on people’s data on the purchase of medicines.
Data protection experts fear that the data market will become uncontrollable.
“There is a data protection program that binds the use of prescription drug data in any case to the consent of the person concerned.
It has to be in the hands of an independent person, otherwise we entrust the chicken coop to the fox," said Richard Dick, the author of the Washington Post's drug-prescribing program.
Insurance companies make insurance and the amounts paid in the case of insurance events dependent on the health status of the interested parties, and if the risk is assessed as too great, the insurance does not even close with it.
In the past, they sent the patients for medical examination and concluded the contract only when they knew their results.
Ten years ago, Dick invented a much cheaper procedure: based on the identification number, the customer from pharmacies can easily find out what drugs the person in question has bought in the last year and a half, from which the program itself derives, what he suffers from the disease and what his state of health is.
For example, if you regularly buy a large amount of cholesterol-lowering drugs, it indicates that you have virtually uncontrollably high blood fat levels, which will immediately put you in a category with a higher risk.
There are several versions of the program in circulation, some of them also determine the risk coefficient, so there is almost no work left for the insurance company in addition to paperwork, although there are minor difficulties.
Disadvantages include that leaky drugs can be used for several purposes, some compounds are, for example, useful against migraines or hot flushes, but are also effective against depression.
These are, from the point of view of commercial insurance companies, a significant risk-increasing factor, whereas the difficulties mentioned above are not.
In order to request and process the data, special companies have been created, which, before obtaining the necessary information from the pharmacies, ask the patient for permission.
They are now being forced to do so by the authorities, even though they have not been punished for their carelessness so far.
Some companies have recently also been processing the results of laboratory tests, which combine with data on the drugs used, thanks to which they can provide an even more accurate picture of the health status of patients.
More and more companies have access to the data, at the same time it will be more and more difficult to control their use.
There is a special law on the protection of health data, but its effectiveness applies only to providers of health services and insurance companies.
The bill, which gives the authorities the power to control even companies that specialize in providing data, is before Congress.
Richard Dick acknowledges that this is not enough: therefore, he has developed his program so that the transfer of data is bound to the express consent of the person concerned.
The other thing is that he can hardly refuse the permit in question, otherwise the insurance companies will not conclude a contract with him.
So chickens are a little bit referred to the list of good will.
